  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>&lt;paulproteus&gt; We don't have a strong story for showing the wannahelper some
useful info when they click that they want to help
&lt;paulproteus&gt; It'd be nice to give them concrete next steps, maybe, rather than
just let them queue up in the list.
&lt;aldeka&gt; Hm.
&lt;paulproteus&gt; Like show them a random 3 bugs from the project in a modal
overlay, and/or say, "If you're looking for the source code, go to <a href="http://xyz">http://xyz</a>"
&lt;aldeka&gt; I thought the whole idea was "I want to help; tell me what to do!".
&lt;aldeka&gt; Not sure how much we can remove humans from that process.
&lt;paulproteus&gt; I guess one thing we can do is let the project maintainer write
some free-form text to show people.
&lt;paulproteus&gt; "Hi! Here are the essentials: We will reach out to you, now that
you've clicked the button. If you want to find us, join the #openhatch IRC
channel. Right now! I mean it. Click here: <a href="http://openhatch.org/contact/">http://openhatch.org/contact/</a>" is
something I would put there.
&lt;aldeka&gt; Heh. :)
&lt;paulproteus&gt; I know the following is radical, but:
&lt;paulproteus&gt; If you click the button, that overlay could be the default action.
&lt;paulproteus&gt; Then it says: "To make sure we reach out to you, you'll have to
click this button and log in. Then you'll get a chance to say more about
yourself. CLICK IT!"
&lt;paulproteus&gt; i.e. that way, you can click the button and not immediately see a
(possibly scary) "Log in!" thing
&lt;paulproteus&gt; I'm afraid of dropping people on the floor at the "Log in!" point.
&lt;paulproteus&gt; I can try to run some numbers and see how many people get to the
login but then fail to log in, if that would help motivate/demotivate the
suggestion.
&lt;paulproteus&gt; (get to the login *after* clicking an I Want To Help link, that is)</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg2395">msg2395 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: aldeka</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-08-27.21:34:36</th>
