  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Spec for the mockups:

1.) The IWH button should only appear if you're not already marked as a
contributor to the project.
2.) If you *are* marked as a contributor, a orange "I maintain this project"
button should appear.
3.) When you click the IWH button, an optional form field should appear asking
what sorts of things you would be interested in helping with. This extra
information would then appear for current maintainers in the 'prospective
helpers' contacting interface.
4.) After you click IWH, a rectangular green badge saying "I want to help"
should appear in the place of the button.
5.) If you are marked as a contributor of a project, a rectangular blue badge
should appear saying "I am a contributor" (above where the maintainer button
appears).
6.) If you click the maintainer button, a rectangular orange "I am a maintainer"
badge should appear in place of the button (below the contributor badge).

Optional: Asheesh suggested having an overlay that appears after you click the
IWH button, before even the optional extra field appears, where maintainers can
write a special note to IWHelpers.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
